div.p:
1. That things Indifferent are so called from their
general Nature, and not as if in practice and use, and
all manner of cases, they always were so, and never unlawful;
for that they may be by Accident and Circumstance;
being lawful unlawful, expedient or inexpedient,
as they are used and applied.

1. This is no argument to those that say there is nothing
Indifferent in the Worship of God;Answer. for then there
is nothing in it matter of Christian Liberty;
